entries.femaleVariant: Hey.
Hey. Wow, it's been a while since I heard that voice.

entries.maleVariant: Hey. How's it goin'?
Watchin' the "Little Big Corporats" season finale. You?

entries.femaleVariant: Hey.
Hey, V, look, um, season finale of "Little Big Corporats" is on in a minute. So, uh, call you back later, huh?
Hey.
You've got some nerve!
Hey, this is Judy. Sorry, can't answer because I'm busy packin' my shit.
If you don't know why, means I just didn't want to tell you.
Hey.
Randy! Leave the damn dog alone, I said!
Hey.
Hey. Uh, bad time. Can it wait?
How's it going?
Heey. Think I oughta ask you the same.
Hello.
Well about damn time, V! Been trying to reach you for days now!
Had a lot on my mind, a lot going on.
entries.maleVariant: Had a lot on my mind, a... a lot going on.

entries.femaleVariant: What the hell happened to you?
Got rid of the biochip.
Just feeling down.
Not about to even try explaining..
Got the chip outta my head.
Was just... havin' a hell of a rough time.
Not even gonna try to explain.
No. Really? You're joking!
No. Just had the… procedure. Not feeling so hot.
Should've called! You really should've called.
So I made a deal with Arasaka. They removed the chip.
Where are you?
Orbital station. Arasaka's. Think I'm gonna puke.
V, you idiot! Get back down to Earth! Now!
The fuck, V? It's like you're trying to piss me off.
Made a deal with Arasaka, they got the chip out of my head. So go ahead, get pissed if you want to. I already feel like shit.
Great to hear your voice.
Doctor up here's a real bitch.
Think I might be going nuts.
It's so good to hear your voice. I'm just... I'm so glad you're here – there.
Doctor up here's a real cunt, lemme tell you. Torturin' me with stupid tests, all the time.
You know, I think I might be losin' my mind.
entries.maleVariant: You know, think I might be losin' my mind.

entries.femaleVariant: Don't take anything they give you! Nothin'!
Might sound cliché, but feels like they're hidin' somethin'.
OK – enough. Get a grip, grab a shuttle and get your ass back home.
Fuuuuck…
This place, it's killin' me.
V! You even hear what you're saying? I mean, Arasaka! You let 'em take you into orbit, dig around in your head, and now you think to complain?
Fuck, V. I thought you were dead.
Really wanna see you again.
entries.maleVariant: I really wanna see you again.

entries.femaleVariant: I don't know what I'll do if I every find out you're gone.
I'm gonna hang up. And I wanna see you back on Earth. In hours. No – now!
Got rid of the biochip.
I'm down, doing badly.
Cheer me up?
Got rid of the biochip. It's outta my head.
Oh. That good or bad news?
Don't know that yet. Just had the... procedure.
No, I'm not. Not doin' hot at all.
So come on over. We'll talk, figure somethin' out.
Made a deal with Arasaka. They removed the chip.
Cheer me up, will ya?
entries.maleVariant: Hey, cheer me up, will ya?

entries.femaleVariant: Over comms? Nah, c'mon. Where are you?
Made a deal with Arasaka. They cut out the chip. I'm somewhere in orbit. Some backwater trajectory.
Which hospital you at?
Ah, not at a hospital. Arasaka orbital station.
entries.maleVariant: Not at a hospital. Arasaka orbital station.

entries.femaleVariant: Tell me which one. I'll fly out an' get you back here.
So glad I got you.
Don't know which one.
Going a little nuts up here.
So glad I've got you.
Yeah, good, and I don't wanna lose you. So take good care of yourself until I get there.
Joss and the kids – how are they? And is Randy back?
Yeah, yeah, he's back. It's all fine.
Look, I gotta go. Gonna find you, hear me?
I don't even know the station's name.
entries.maleVariant: Don't even know the station's name.

entries.femaleVariant: Don't worry, I'll find it. I'll figure it out.
Nobody tells me anything here.
You just sit tight. Take care of yourself, stay outta trouble till I get there.
You know, I think I might be going a little crazy up here.
entries.maleVariant: You know, think I might be going a little crazy up here.

entries.femaleVariant: And you can finish doing that on Earth.
Wow. Been a while, V.
Been goin' through some shit. Lotta changes.
What happened? You all right?
Randy! Get the hell out!
Give me the name of the station. I'll fly up and get you.
They'll never let you in.
Like hell, they won't!

entries.maleVariant: Got rid of the biochip.

entries.femaleVariant: [pl_pl]Mam deprechę.
entries.maleVariant: Feeling pretty down.

entries.femaleVariant: [pl_pl]Zgadnij, gdzie jestem.
entries.maleVariant: Guess where I am.
Got rid of the biochip.
No. You're fuckin' kidding!
Got a big ol' hole in my head. They filled it with, I dunno, cables 'n' shit.
I'm just really depressed.
Oh… I know! Let's fly out to my place in Florida. A little sun, a little change'll do you good.
Had enough change recently. I'm sittin' in orbit. Just had the biochip removed.
Guess where I am.
How many tries do I get?
Never mind, doesn't matter, you'd never guess. I'm in orbit.
Fuuuck. Need anything?
You.
All right, all right. Don't worry about a thing.

entries.femaleVariant: [pl_pl]Cieszę się, że cię mam.
entries.maleVariant: So glad I got you.

entries.femaleVariant: [pl_pl]Jak się skończyły "Korpo-karły"?
entries.maleVariant: How did "Little Big Corporats" end?

entries.femaleVariant: [pl_pl]Trochę mi tu odbija.
entries.maleVariant: Going a little nuts up here.
I'm so glad I've got you.
V, you are the best thing this planet's got going for her. So come back down.
Wish I were there with you now.
OK. I'm gonna hang up now, make a few calls, get you back to Night City. Sound good?
Take care, V. See you soon!
How'd "Little Big Corporats" turn out?
Oh, not about to spoil it for you. You can catch the reruns when you get back.
You'll watch it again with me?
Hah! Will I!
Honest? Think I might be losin' my mind here.
You there alone?
No. There's some doctor here. Real bitch. But I guess that's it. So, yeah, pretty much alone.
You shouldn't be, not now. Not good.

entries.femaleVariant: It's Arasaka, V. Not Rippers Without Borders. Don't you dare let them hurt you.

entries.maleVariant: Trauma Team? Sit tight, I know people, gonna make some calls.
Arasaka.
Oh shit!
Yep.

entries.femaleVariant: Randy! Get the hell outta here!

entries.maleVariant: Where are you? Which hospital?
Dunno. Orbital station. Arasaka.

entries.femaleVariant: Listen, I'm not doing so hot.
So – what's up with you?
Listen... I'm stuck in a shithole. It sucks, hard.
entries.maleVariant: Listen... I'm… I'm stuck in a shithole. It sucks, hard.

entries.femaleVariant: How's things at your end?
I'm in the middle of a meeting with Mitch. He wants me to hang up, he's signaling wildly.
Tell him to get lost. An' tell him I said that.
He says hello.
To you and your venerable mother.
So leave the shithole. Come home.
Not that simple.
entries.maleVariant: It's not that simple.

entries.femaleVariant: "No" is a nice word, beautiful sometimes. You should use it more often.
Sorry. Mitch is about to blow a fuse. I'll have to call you back.
Yeah, sure. Nothing important.
Look, need to talk to somebody. I'm sittin' up in orbit and it sucks.
entries.maleVariant: Look, I need to talk to somebody. I'm sittin' up in orbit and it sucks.

entries.femaleVariant: I need to talk.
OK, never mind. Have fun.
Will do. See ya!
What the hell you doin' up there?
Oh, long story.
entries.maleVariant: Long story...

entries.femaleVariant: Well, if it sucks, come back down.
Gotta wait for the end of the stupid tests.
entries.maleVariant: Gotta wait for the end of these stupid tests.

entries.femaleVariant: Ah, don't have to do a thing. Just, y'know, break the fuck outta there.
OK, it's starting. Gotta go.
No.
Just wanted to talk.
Um, not really. It's actually important.
Just wanted to talk.
If this is V, I'll call you. Maybe, baby. When I'm done being pissed off.
Wait, what? What's the problem?
Oh, I spoke with Viktor. So please stop acting surprised!
Where the hell are you?!
Aboard a station in orbit.
Stop yelling at me.
Sitting on an Arasaka orbital station. No idea which one.
Hey, stop yelling at me.
You piece of shit. You're lucky we're not face-to-face!
Seriously… Where are you?!
Like I could give a shit which one! You're in trouble. Again. Alone. You could have asked for help!
Had my reasons.
Ugh. Fuck. Enough! Just stop pissing me off. Return to Earth, now, before they hurt you.
Nice to hear your voice again.
It's good to hear yours too, idiot. Now come home.
Not feeling great, but I'm alive.
Got rid of the biochip.
Yeah, so, to be honest, been better.
Got rid of the biochip.
How's Misty?
How's Misty?
Well, after you left, she went off to visit her folks – for a while, most likely.
Got a postcard from her, from Warsaw. There's a polar bear on it.
Tell her I said hi when she gets back.
You'll tell her yourself.
Arasaka do it?
Yep. Sittin' on their orbital station.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah. Sittin' on their orbital station.

entries.femaleVariant: All right. So once you get back, pay me a visit, huh? You're gonna need a thorough check-up.
What am I supposed to do long-distance, over the phone?
I just wanted to talk, Vik.
Look, we go back long enough that you know I'm no good at this stuff. And Misty's out of town.
What'm I supposed to do?
Get a grip, make a decision. You already showed yourself and me you can do it.
Huh. Thanks for the pep talk, Vik. Sounds like a plan.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah. Thanks for the pep talk, Vik. Sounds like a plan.

entries.femaleVariant: Sorry. Like I said, bad time. Have to call you back.
Fuck!
Sorry. Look, can't talk now, gonna have to call you back.
